{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_armadillo_ver01/data/sn83004231/00414180863/1949051401/0296.xml":{"full_text":"Grand Attorney\nKjjiv JaKflj^fc\nflfr\nHe f-'\nV HV JkT'm\n\u2022\u00ab^VsfW s ivM\u00bbV v r V\nA veteran barrister and for many\norders the Grand Attorney is S. D.\nMcGill of Jacksonville, one of the\nmost distinguished members of th_'\nbar. White or Black, in America to\nday, He is pictured here.\nColonel McGill, who still enjoys\na lucrative law practice at Jackson\nville. is a great Floridian. He has\nhad many honors to come his way,\nprincipal among these being the\nGrand Attorney of the Knights of\nPythias of Florida, for longer than\nmany of the Pythian veterans can\nremember, and in addition, he is\nthe Supreme Lodge Grand Attor\nney, a position he has held for many\nyears with honor and much ability.\nHe is present at these annual\nState grand lodge sessions in this\nFriendly City of West Palm Beach,\nwhere he is lending his able hand\nin steering the wheels which operate\nthis ''rand Old Order.\u201d\nHelp The Scouts\nStop Shop at Kings\nKING\u2019S SUNDRIES\n425 N. W. 20th STREET\nAlways a Crowd\nSUGGESTIONS:\nTry Our Delicious Grilled Sandwiches\nand\nSouthern Dairies Ice Cream\nArthur King, Prop.\nr\nOur candies taste better and are better for you\nFind all your favorite fountain treats here Ice\ncold Cokes, rich sundaes, and creamy sodas \u2014Drop\nin at\u2014 a l\nMcQUEEN\u2019S SUNDRIES\n504 N. W. 14th St. (Near sth Are.)\nsetJ\nHi CONSft*OMd\\'IALIsT*SSftVKS\nfi*ssrs* ig-FgMES\nKnights Os Pythias Hold Sta\nMIAMI TIMES, MIAMI, FLORIDA\nPAGE EIGHT\nDeputy Grand\nChancellor\n\u25a0Jbk <3%\nv>\nj Deputy Grand Chancellor Sir J.\nB. Jenkins of West Palm Beach.\nI host city to this annual grand lodge\nsession of the Knights of Pythias of\ni Florida is one of the better known\nand most capable officers of the\norder. He is pictured here.\nHe stands h gh in the community\njand had a large hand in the plann\n-1 Ing of this current grand conclave\nand communication in this great\ncommunity. He is a leader of abili\nty and has had a hand in the pres\nent large growth of the order, and\nnas been an important cog in the\nPythiar. machinery for many v<*ars.\nj He and his aides are to be con\ngratulated for the part they played\nin the entertainment of this grand\nlodge.\nSATURDAY, MAY 14, 1949\nKeeper Os Records\nA youthful .member of the bar\nand one of the nation's most prom\nising lawyers, who is making his\nmark in the fraternal life of Flori\nda, is Attorney Raleford McGriff,\npictured here.\nHe holds the important position *f\nGrand Keeper of Records and Seals\nof the Florida Knights of Pythias,\npresently in session in West Palm\nBeach Monday of this week through\nWednesday. This notable Jaxon,\nwho took over the post when the\norder was somewhat on the decline\nhas done much in Its recession to\nthe top.\nCounsellor McGriff is a practic\ning attorney at Jacksonville, where\nhe has made an enviable record for\nhimself, and is associated in the\nMcGill and McGill Law Firm in\nlacksonville. He is turning in a re\nmarkable service for the order, an<l\nis here now carrying. He is one of\nthe youngest of the grand lodge of-\nPeers, and we say here \u201cMore Pow\ner To The Younger Men of The Or\nder.\u201d He serves most certainly as\nan inspiration to them.\nPATRONIZE\nOUR\nADVERTISERS\nRANDOLPH\u2019S SUNDRIES\n801 N. W. 2nd Ave. (Cor. Bth St.)\nSouthern Dairies Ice Cream, Sodas, Patent Medicines\nCigars, Cigarettes and other Sundries\nOPEN 8 a.m. to MIDNIGHT\nJoseph and Marie Randolph, Proprietors\nMake Our Store Your Shopping Center\nTHE COMMUHITY DRUG STORE\nCut Rate Drugs\nPRESCRIPTIONS\n0 Carefully Compounded\nC M. Jollhrette, Sr., Reg. Pkarm., Prop.\n6740 N.W. 15th Ave*\nPhone 78 3434 Next to Libsitji Hisatrs\nWe Call For and Deliver Prescriptions\nSeal test Ice Cream\nState Grand\nChancellor\njxs v- '-avx'-X\u2019\nmFM jjjgf\nColonel B. L. Goines, State Grand\nChancellor of the Knights of Py\nthias of Florida, is leading one of\nthe largest Grand Lodge Sessions in\nthe long history of the order, this\nweek, Monday, Tuesday and Wed\nnesday. May 16, 17 and 18, in West\nPalm Beach. \u201cThe City Beautiful.\u201d\nHe is pictured here.\nSir Goines is a resident of Jack\nsonville, and is regarded as one of\nits most substantial and influential\ncitizens and is active in the various\nuplift activities of his city, com\nmunity and the state. He is one of\nthe great Pythian leaders and is\ndoing a wonderful service of lead\nership and guidance of the order, es\npecially since the order has taken\non its new birth. Under Grand Chan\ncellor Goines Pythianism in this\nstate has taken on new birth and\nis again one of the powers among\nthe fraternal orders of the state.\nHe is a fine leader, kindly, under\nstanding and is destined to go much\nfarther in the realm of fraternal\nism not only in Florida, hut in the\nnation.\nThe Florida Grand Chancellor is\nsaluted and wished a most prosper\nous grand lodge session in West\nPalm Beach next week?\nMODERN\nThe South\u2019s FIRST\nand ONLY\nAIR-CONDITIONED\nNEGRO THEATRE\nJ BY SPIKE WASHINGTON\nJACKSONVILLE, Fla. For\nI ANP) \u2014Knights of Pythias of Flori\nda, hailing from every nook and\ncranny of this \u201cLand of Sunshine\nand Flowers,\u201d will soon be converg\ning on the \u201cHospitality City of\nFlorida,\u201d West Palm Beach, where\n\u2022\u2018summer spends the winter.\u201d\nThese leaders in fraternal circles\nof the state, headed by the genial\nJaxon, Sir B. L. Goines, who is do\ning a remarkably fine work \"in the\npost of Grand Chancellor and their\nfollowers, who are loyal to the core\nand industrious to the nth degree,\nand who have played a large part\nin the growth and development of\nthe order during the past several\nyears, are making ready for their\nannual Grand Lodge Sessions,\nwhich will be held in West Palm\nBeach on Tuesday, Wednesday and\nThursday, May 17, 18, and 19, in\nclusive.\nThe lodges of the order at West\nPalm Beach will be host to the\ngreat gathering of these fraternal\ndignitaries, and host to the women's\ndepartments, the Courts of Calantho\nand others of their units, combined\nwith the uniform rank, will be the\ngood women of the several Courts\nin West Palm Beach. The leaders\nof the host city have laid their\nplans carefully for the coming a\nthese state orders, and it is promised\nthat this session will be the finest,\nand most fruitful one in many years.\nAll eyes are now focused on West\nPalm Beach by officers and mem\nbers of the order.\nOFFICERS STAND HARD BY\nStanding beside Grand Chancellor\nGoines, who has come from the\nranks to the highest honor witkia\nthe gift of the state organization of\nKnights of Pythias, are several \u00ab>f\nthe great fraternal men and women\nof the nation, regardless of craft\nthey are affiliated with. There are\nsuch notables as Edward A. Potts\ndamer, Tallahassee businessman,\nchurchman, civic leader and large\nproperty holder, who has establish\ned a record, and an enviable one.\nhaving served the state order as\ntreasurer for better than 40 y\u00abara;\nwhich is believed to be a national\nrecord; Attorney Releford McGriif.\nbrilliant young Jacksonville barris\nter, who has a bright future in la v\nand fraternal affairs, and is Grand\nKeeper of Records and Seals; Grand\nAttorney S. D. McGill, also of Jack\nsonville, and for many years, grand\nattorney of the state and for a stm-\nDeputy Grand\nChancellor\nI Jf\nmmmm\nfppiltes! Ji\n-HI I \u2018WHP\n\u20141 mil Hum i\\ m\nSir Vasco Reaves, like all of the\nother officers of the Knights of\nPythias Grand Lodge, is a vetroan\nand able officer of the craft, and\nhas been n potent factor in the or\nder's growth for many years. He i*\npictured here.\nSir Reaves is a Deputy Grand\nChancellor and has done a tremen\ndously fine work In his capacity for\nmany years. He la a leading resi\ndent of his community which is Ft.\nMeade and brings to the Grand\nLodge the goodwill and beat wishes\nof every Pythian in his area. It is\nfitting that such a notable\nleader and officer be commended\nand saluted for what he has meant\nto the order In other years and.\npresently.\nHe will play the part assigned\nhim at theee annual sessions, .Mon\nday through Wednesday, this wreck.","height":"27770","width":"19192"}}
